&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;King’s College Hospital NHS Foundation Trust part of King&#39;s Health Partners Academic Health Sciences Centre (AHSC), is one of the UK’s largest and busiest teaching hospitals with a turnover of nearly £1 billion, 1.5 million patient contacts a year and more than 12,600 staff based across 5 main sites in South East London and Kent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust provides a full range of local hospital services across its different sites, and specialist services from King’s College Hospital (KCH) site in Camberwell and the Princess Royal University Hospital (PRUH) site in Bromley, Orpington Hospital, and some services at Beckenham Beacon and Queen Mary’s Sidcup.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kings College Hospital is recognized internationally for its work in Liver Disease and Transplantation with the Liver service regarded as the largest comprehensive clinical liver programme in the world. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking to appoint two Junior Clinical Fellow to work within King’s liver Hepato-biliary &amp; pancreatic Surgery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidates will work under the supervision of the HPB consultant surgeons. The post-holder will gain a broad experience in all aspects of HPB surgery with opportunities to combine research in a large hepato-pancreato-biliary surgical unit with clinical commitment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The posts are offered on a 1 year fixed term contract renewable for a maximum of 2 years in total. The post-holders will receive training in duties of the post as necessary.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMr Parthi SrinivasanJob titleConsultant Liver Transplant &amp; Clinical Lead for HPB SurgeonEmail addressparthi.srinivasan@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
